      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">In-ground gardening in the Mesilla Valley means dealing with pH levels above 8, caliche hardpan a few inches down, and soil that either bakes into concrete or turns to mud during monsoons. Raised beds bypass all of that.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">We build the structure, fill it with a soil mix designed for what you want to grow, and connect drip irrigation so watering is consistent and efficient. The result is a garden that produces instead of struggles.</p>
